      <hedline>
        <hl1>Enemies, A Love Story</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Savannah Jahrling letter on Andrew Sullivan's April 16 column holds religious right likes individuals but feels it must keep larger masses of humanity at bay (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>That people on the religious right are ''really quite nice,'' as Andrew Sullivan thinks he has discovered, is no secret at all. As right-wingers themselves are fond of saying, they like individuals. It's the larger masses of humanity that they believe must be held at bay.</p>
        <p>Savannah Jahrling  Madison, Wis.</p>
      </block>
